@startuml consolidator-heartbeat-flow
!include _standard-style.puml

title Consolidation Flow with In-Process Heartbeat\n(host obs-api owns observations.db)

actor User
participant "Dashboard\n(server.js, container)" as D <<api>>
participant "Observations API\n(host, :12436)" as A <<api>>
database ".observations/\nconsolidation-\nheartbeat.json" as HB <<storage>>
database ".observations/\nobservations.db" as DB <<storage>>
participant "ObservationConsolidator\n(in-process)" as OC <<core>>

== Trigger ==

User -> D: POST /api/consolidation/run
D -> A: POST /api/consolidation/run\n(forward via host.docker.internal:12436)
note right
  Dashboard is a thin forwarder.
  Consolidation runs in-process inside
  the obs-api server, which already
  owns the SQLite handle — no spawn,
  no second writer, no WAL race.
end note
activate A

A -> A: coalesce concurrent triggers\n(_consolidationPromise)
A -> HB: write {pid, startedAt,\n  lastHeartbeat, args}
A -> A: tap process.stderr so any\nconsolidator log line refreshes\nlastStderrAt + lastMessage
loop every ~2s
    A -> HB: refresh lastHeartbeat
end

A -> OC: run({includeToday}) | consolidateDay(date) | synthesizeInsights()
activate OC
loop for each undigested day
    OC -> DB: read observations
    OC -> OC: LLM theme grouping
    OC -> DB: write digest
    A -> HB: bump (last stderr line\n  becomes lastMessage)
end
OC --> A: result
deactivate OC

A -> HB: unlink (graceful exit)
A --> D: { success, ok, digests, created, updated }
deactivate A
D --> User: same payload

== Status ==

User -> D: GET /api/consolidation/status
D -> A: forward GET
A -> HB: read heartbeat
HB --> A: { pid, ageMs, alive, lastMessage } | null
A --> D: { totalObs, undigested, …,\n  inflight: { … } | null }
D --> User: same payload

== Auto-consolidation (host-side, every 30 min) ==

D -> A: GET /api/consolidation/status\n(via _fetchObsApi)
A --> D: pendingPast count
alt pendingPast >= 10
    D -> A: POST /api/consolidation/run
end

@enduml
